# Color Variables

## Overview

Always use CSS variables for colors instead of hardcoded hex values. This ensures consistency, maintainability, and easier theming.

## Brand Colors

The project defines brand colors in `app/globals.css`:

```css
:root {
  /* Brand Colors */
  --brand: #e85a4f;
  --brand-hover: #d64a3f;
  --brand-light: #f5a29b;
}
```

These are mapped to Tailwind classes via `@theme inline`:

```css
@theme inline {
  --color-brand: var(--brand);
  --color-brand-hover: var(--brand-hover);
  --color-brand-light: var(--brand-light);
}
```

## Usage

### ✅ Good - Use CSS variable classes

```tsx
// Background
<div className="bg-brand">...</div>
<button className="bg-brand hover:bg-brand-hover">...</button>

// Text
<span className="text-brand">...</span>

// Border and ring
<input className="focus:border-brand focus:ring-brand" />
```

### ❌ Bad - Hardcoded hex values

```tsx
// Don't use hardcoded colors
<div className="bg-[#E85A4F]">...</div>
<button className="bg-[#e85a4f] hover:bg-[#D64A3F]">...</button>
<span className="text-[#E85A4F]">...</span>
```

